title: Google\Cloud\Asset\V1beta1\GcsDestination
name: GcsDestination
description:
A Cloud Storage location.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.asset.v1beta1.GcsDestination

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.uri
params.description: The uri of the Cloud Storage object. It's the same uri that is used by gsutil. For example: "gs://bucket_name/object_name". See Viewing and Editing Object Metadata for more information.

params.name: data.uri_prefix
params.description: The uri prefix of all generated Cloud Storage objects. For example: "gs://bucket_name/object_name_prefix". Each object uri is in format: "gs://bucket_name/object_name_prefix// and only contains assets for that type. starts from 0. For example: "gs://bucket_name/object_name_prefix/google.compute.disk/0" is the first shard of output objects containing all google.compute.disk assets. An INVALID_ARGUMENT error will be returned if file with the same name "gs://bucket_name/object_name_prefix" already exists.
